6
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:43,430
The teaching speaks
about a man who cannot see.

7
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:46,354
In which direction should he pray?

8
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:51,957
A blind, a man who can't see where
the West, East, North, or South is,

9
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:56,240
and can't locate himself.
Who could that be for instance?

10
00:01:56,400 --> 00:02:00,997
A man who can't locate himself,
who can't find the cardinal points:

11
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:03,629
someone who is on a boat at sea,
in the desert,

12
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:08,153
in a place from which he can't
orient himself, is considered blind.

13
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,754
He can't know where to turn to,

14
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:12,037
therefore he has a problem praying.

15
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:16,399
A disoriented person should turn
his heart to His Father in Heaven.

16
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:19,792
If you don't know
where Jerusalem is, the Western Wall,

17
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:22,077
where the Temple was,
what should you do?

18
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:24,630
What does the teaching suggest?

19
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,759
To turn our hearts
to Our Father in Heaven.

20
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,310
I want to expose this problem
to you,

21
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:32,079
I find it interesting.

22
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:34,073
Think about it,

23
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,715
