00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:41,630
Are you Ok?

507
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:43,434
Can l talk to you?

508
00:39:43,560 --> 00:39:46,758
One sec, let me finish
and l'll be with you.

509
00:39:47,040 --> 00:39:50,829
One more thing about the picture,
it can stay like this,

510
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:54,431
but they need it urgently
for tomorrow morning

511
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:56,950
to see it and then have a print.

512
00:39:57,120 --> 00:40:00,796
Are they stressed about it?
- Very, they need it tomorrow.

513
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:05,831
So we move the phone number
to here and erase this part.

514
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:07,872
Fine, l'll do it.

515
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:11,710
Great. l'm going to the machine.
- Thanks.

516
00:40:11,840 --> 00:40:12,876
Sit down.

517
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:14,916
What is it?

518
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:20,031
l want to apologize
for what happened, Aaron.

519
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:23,793
l told you, don't apologize.
Forget it, it's past.

520
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:26,192
Don't worry about it, really.

521
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:28,631
Can l see Grandpa?
Will you take me there?

522
00:40:28,920 --> 00:40:32,072
He's studying, l can't
take you there. lt disturbs him.

523
00:40:32,200 --> 00:40:36,319
We don't disturb him when he studies.
- l want to talk to him.

524
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:39,199
Let me show you what l've done.

525
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:41,553
Aaron.
- One sec.

526
00:40:42,160 --> 00:40:43,355
Look at this.

527
00:40:53,240 --> 00:40:57,234
Do me a favor, bring
that gray folder over from up there.

528
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:04,150
This one?
- Yes.

529
00:41:05,080 --> 00:41:08,869
Pull that paper out.
This page from the printer.

530
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:20,356
Read.

531
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:22,636
Read out loud.

532
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:28,677
"Please say Tehilim for our dear
father, brother, and son,

533
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:32,760
"Eli Ben Sarah Frankel,
who's missing from home.

534
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:36,191
"May Repentance, Prayer, and Charity

535
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:38,152
"ease the pain."

536
00:41:38,280 --> 00:41:41,796
"May Repentance, Prayer, and Charity
ease the pain, with God's help."

537
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:47,153
lt's important people pray for him.
So l ordered 200 psalms books.

538
00:41:47,280 --> 00:41:50,398
We'll print these, glue them here
and give them to people.

539
00:41:50,520 --> 00:41:51,431
Yes.

540
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:55,080
Yes.

541
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:57,552
Aaron, take me to Grandpa.

542
00:42:13,040 --> 00:42:15,430
Father, sorry to disturb you.

543
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:19,791
Menachem needs to talk to you.

544
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:22,070
Sit down.

545
00:42:24,040 --> 00:42:25,076
Grandpa.

546
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:29,634
l wanted to apologize
for what happened.

547
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:34,116
Mom's going through a lot lately,
she's not herself.

548
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:37,080
l know, it's not her fault.

549
00:42:37,600 --> 00:42:40,069
lt's how she's been brought up.

550
00:42:41,080 --> 00:42:42,673
But you are a good boy.

551
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:44,674
You'll know what to do.

552
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:48,874
You know good from bad,
what's important and what's not.

553
00:42:50,720 --> 00:42:52,359
You'll know how to repair,

554
00:42:54,560 --> 00:42:56,040
to make it right.

555
00:43:05,480 --> 00:43:07,676
Before you were born
we came here a lot.

556
00:43:09,040 --> 00:43:10,190
You feel good?

557
00:43:11,320 --> 00:43:12,470
l'm glad we came.

558
00:43:15,160 --> 00:43:17,072
You're hungry?
Wanna eat something?

559
00:43:17,480 --> 00:43:18,516
Yes.

560
00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:12,710
Mom,

561
00:44:13,360 --> 00:44:15,431
get up, you should go to sleep.

562
00:44:15,800 --> 00:44:17,314
Come here.

563
00:44:17,440 --> 00:44:21,798
Get up, let me help you.
- No, l want a hug.

564
00:44:21,920 --> 00:44:24,674
Get up, it's late Mom.
- Soon.

565
00:44:25,360 --> 00:44:28,000
Go to your bed.
- ln a minute.

566
00:44:28,120 --> 00:44:31,192
You're on the couch, go to bed.
- Soon.

567
00:44:34,560 --> 00:44:36,074
Good night.

568
00:44:47,000 --> 00:44:50,789
Good morning. Alma Frankel?
- Yes. l've been waiting since seven.

569
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:54,120
We just made it.
l've brought back the car.

570
00:44:54,240 --> 00:44:56,357
Why here and not to the garage?

571
00:44:56,920 --> 00:44:58,479
l was told to bring it here.

572
00:44:58,600 --> 00:45:03,277
Can you sign here?
Where do you want me to put it?

573
00:45:03,400 --> 00:45:06,074
Put it at the end of the street.

574
00:45:06,200 --> 00:45:10,035
Sorry, l've to put it at Simhoni 3.
lt's the address l got.

575
00:45:10,160 --> 00:45:13,358
l understand, but l don't want
my kids to see it.

576
00:45:13,480 --> 00:45:17,190
l can't move it cause it's broken.
So please, put it there.

577
00:45:17,320 --> 00:45:19,312
Down there?
- Yes, l'll show you.

578
00:45:19,840 --> 00:45:20,956
Shaul!

579
00:45:38,840 --> 00:45:43,869
Where exactly? l'll tell the driver.
- Down there on the left.

580
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:51,358
Park it around the left corner.
On the left there is a parking spot.

581
00:45:54,080 --> 00:45:55,912
Have a good day.
- Thank you so much.

582
00:46:14,800 --> 00:46:18,510
... these pants?
Sport shoes? What do you want?

583
00:46:18,680 --> 00:46:20,512
This one.
- That?

584
00:46:21,280 --> 00:46:23,033
Sure?
- Yes.

585
00:46:23,240 --> 00:46:26,711
You do it yourself?
- Yes, l'll manage.

586
00:46:27,200 --> 00:46:29,715
You have everything in your bag?
- Yes.

587
00:46:29,840 --> 00:46:32,753
You have to hurry up, you know?

588
00:46:34,520 --> 00:46:36,352
David, are you ready?
- Not yet.

589
00:46:37,320 --> 00:46:39,755
What's up?
- l'm well. Good morning.

590
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:41,553
That fits? Good.

591
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:43,475
What?

592
00:46:43,640 --> 00:46:45,552
l said, good morning.
- l did too.

593
00:46:46,800 --> 00:46:50,316
l have to go.
Where are your shoes?

594
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:54,073
You'll manage?
- Yes.

595
00:46:55,320 --> 00:46:59,360
He wants to eat too.
Try to be on time.

596
00:46:59,480 --> 00:47:00,709
You say bye?

597
00:47:03,000 --> 00:47:04,354
You tell me bye too?

598
00:47:12,560 --> 00:47:14,153
Here, put on your kippa.

599
00:47:24,840 --> 00:47:27,196
David, no!
- Why?

600
00:47:27,360 --> 00:47:28,430
Let's go this way.

601
00:47:28,560 --> 00:47:29,914
Why?
- Because.

602
00:47:32,320 --> 00:47:33,800
Hurry up.

603
00:47:37,720 --> 00:47:39,996
You said you'd get me some food.

604
00:47:40,240 --> 00:47:43,517
Get something at school.
- l'm really hungry.

605
00:47:43,960 --> 00:47:45,952
Eat at school and later at home.

606
00:47:59,080 --> 00:48:00,594
Take your bag.

607
00:48:01,920 --> 00:48:05,152
Go to the station, it's late.
- Aren't you coming?

608
00:48:05,280 --> 00:48:06,600
l'm coming later.

609
00:48:06,720 --> 00:48:10,157
You're really coming later?
- Yes, l start late today.

610
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:12,274
Go to the bus stop.

611
00:48:14,120 --> 00:48:15,713
Why aren't you coming?

612
00:48:16,760 --> 00:48:18,672
Don't miss the bus.
- l won't.

613
00:48:25,320 --> 00:48:26,879
Wait inside.

614
00:50:31,880 --> 00:50:33,234
What are you doing here?

615
00:50:39,600 --> 00:50:40,829
l came to see you.

616
00:50:41,000 --> 00:50:42,354
Did you wait long?

617
00:50:42,720 --> 00:50:43,756
Yes.

618
00:50:43,960 --> 00:50:47,556
You should have called.
My Dad's at home, you can't come up.

619
00:50:49,200 --> 00:50:51,590
l wanted to be with you,
can l come in?

620
00:50:52,400 --> 00:50:56,838
Maybe later. Want to come later?
- What about now?

621
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:58,992
No, my Dad's home now.

622
00:50:59,320 --> 00:51:00,515
Ok.

623
00:51:01,240 --> 00:51:03,357
So you come later?
- Ok.

624
00:51:11,760 --> 00:51:13,160
Can l come in?

625
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:18,116
What do you want?

626
00:51:21,960 --> 00:51:23,110
lt's for you.

627
00:51:24,440 --> 00:51:25,794
l don't want water.

628
00:51:33,880 --> 00:51:35,837
l can't sleep.

629
00:51:37,000 --> 00:51:39,640
You want to talk?
- What do you want to talk about?

630
00:51:40,680 --> 00:51:42,751
l don't know, just talk.

631
00:51:43,480 --> 00:51:46,712
You should wear pajamas.
Why sleep with your clothes on?

632
00:51:46,840 --> 00:51:48,354
You want to tell me something?

633
00:51:49,440 --> 00:51:51,113
No, do you want to?

634
00:51:52,360 --> 00:51:53,350
No.

635
00:51:55,680 --> 00:51:58,434
You want to just talk?
- What about?

636
00:51:59,600 --> 00:52:02,354
l don't know.
lt's important we talk.

637
00:52:02,960 --> 00:52:04,235
We'll talk tomorrow.

638
00:52:04,440 --> 00:52:06,193
How about now?

639
00:52:08,040 --> 00:52:09,679
l just want to be alone.

640
00:52:12,240 --> 00:52:13,230
All right.

641
00:52:28,200 --> 00:52:29,759
David.
- What?

642
00:52:30,080 --> 00:52:32,914
What do you want?
- You should see something.

643
00:52:33,440 --> 00:52:35,830
Show me, then.
- Come.

644
00:52:36,960 --> 00:52:37,996
What is it?

645
00:52:41,800 --> 00:52:44,918
Go back to sleep.
l'll help you sleep. Come.

646
00:52:45,120 --> 00:52:46,839
Come.

647
00:52:46,960 --> 00:52:48,030
What?

648
00:52:48,160 --> 00:52:49,992
You want to eat something?

649
00:52:53,360 --> 00:52:55,875
David, l'm talking to you.

650
00:52:57,080 --> 00:52:58,150
Answer me.

651
00:53:02,280 --> 00:53:04,158
What are you doing?
- Wait.

652
00:53:12,400 --> 00:53:13,311
What's that?

653
00:53:21,120 --> 00:53:24,796
Mom and Orna lied to the bank
and took all Dads' money.

654
00:53:44,000 --> 00:53:45,070
Listen,

655
00:53:45,840 --> 00:53:48,196
don't tell Mom l know.

656
00:53:48,640 --> 00:53:50,438
lt has to stay between us.

657
00:53:51,960 --> 00:53:55,874
lt's our secret. Ok?

658
00:53:59,960 --> 00:54:00,916
Good.

659
00:54:03,360 --> 00:54:05,431
Put the chair back.

660
00:54:17,320 --> 00:54:19,437
Come, lights off.

661
00:54:44,440 --> 00:54:45,715
Menachem.

662
00:54:46,320 --> 00:54:47,800
How are you?

663
00:54:48,240 --> 00:54:49,310
What's up?

664
00:54:49,440 --> 00:54:51,716
How are you?
- Long time no see.

665
00:54:51,840 --> 00:54:55,311
- How do you feel?
- Where were you?

666
00:54:58,000 --> 00:54:59,593
What's up?

667
00:55:00,760 --> 00:55:02,080
lt's been a while.

668
00:55:02,680 --> 00:55:05,593
How's your Mom?
- She's Ok.

669
00:55:06,200 --> 00:55:08,635
Why don't you come to school?
- We'll help you.

670
00:55:10,240 --> 00:55:12,550
And your Dad?
- Debbie, can we talk for a sec?

671
00:55:13,240 --> 00:55:15,038
Wait, where are you going?

672
00:55:16,480 --> 00:55:17,880
Why did you do this?

673
00:55:18,480 --> 00:55:20,073
To be all together.

674
00:55:20,240 --> 00:55:21,879
l don't wanna be with them.

675
00:55:22,000 --> 00:55:24,310
They're your friends.
- l wanted to be with you.

676
00:55:24,440 --> 00:55:28,719
We are together, now.
- l can't be with you.

677
00:55:29,120 --> 00:55:31,316
You don't get it.
l don't wanna see them.

678
00:55:32,040 --> 00:55:33,997
They're your friends. Menachem!

679
00:55:34,920 --> 00:55:36,718
Your friends.
- Forget it!

680
00:55:36,840 --> 00:55:38,274
Come on, Menachem.

681
00:55:48,560 --> 00:55:50,119
Wait for me.

682
00:55:54,920 --> 00:55:57,640
Talk to me.
You haven't talked to me for 20 min.

683
00:56:06,320 --> 00:56:08,880
Stop following me, go home.

684
00:56:09,000 --> 00:56:10,719
But l want to be with you.

685
00:56:11,640 --> 00:56:13,757
Leave me alone, go.

686
00:56:13,920 --> 00:56:17,914
Wait a second!
Hold on. Talk to me.

687
00:56:18,040 --> 00:56:20,032
Debbie, give me a break, go home.

688
00:56:20,200 --> 00:56:23,876
Talk. Why do you do this?
- l don't want you here. Go.

689
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:26,439
You don't love me anymore?
- No.

690
00:56:27,760 --> 00:56:29,592
You really don't?
- No.

691
00:56:33,200 --> 00:56:34,554
Debbie, go home.

692
00:56:35,920 --> 00:56:37,274
Go home.

693
00:56:50,320 --> 00:56:51,276
... that's the situation.

694
00:56:51,480 --> 00:56:56,555
Mom, these talks don't help,
l have practical problems.

695
00:56:56,960 --> 00:56:58,235
How are you, kid?

696
00:56:59,160 --> 00:57:01,595
Hi, Grandma.
- Good to see you.

697
00:57:04,560 --> 00:57:07,029
Happy to see you. How are you?
- Good.

698
00:57:07,160 --> 00:57:09,152
How's school?
- Good.

699
00:57:09,640 --> 00:57:14,396
Alma, be with me.
Pull yourself together.

700
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:17,037
Tell me that you understand,

701
00:57:17,160 --> 00:57:21,040
so that we can move on.

702
00:57:21,280 --> 00:57:26,355
We're a family and we'll face it
together, you're not alone.

703
00:57:26,640 --> 00:57:28,791
You hear me?

704
00:57:29,400 --> 00:57:33,030
Please, for yourself,

705
00:57:33,200 --> 00:57:38,116
for the kids, for me, l can't
see you like this, l'm your mother.

706
00:57:38,240 --> 00:57:41,870
l need your help.
- Fine, fine. You have it.

707
00:57:42,080 --> 00:57:45,437
You have my help in every way.

708
00:57:45,600 --> 00:57:49,389
lf we need legal advice,
whatever we need.

709
00:57:49,520 --> 00:57:52,160
What matters is that
you find yourself again,

710
00:57:52,280 --> 00:57:53,794
you're the key.

711
00:57:53,920 --> 00:57:55,798
l'll be fine again.

712
00:57:56,200 --> 00:57:57,839
Alma, be with me.

713
00:57:58,160 --> 00:58:02,439
Be with me. And understand
what l'm telling you.

714
00:58:02,600 --> 00:58:04,876
l know it's hard, l was there too.

715
00:58:05,040 --> 00:58:08,112
Each situation is different.
But l know what means to be alone.

716
00:59:57,560 --> 01:00:00,155
Spread some egg here.

717
01:00:03,720 --> 01:00:04,870
Don't disturb her.

718
01:00:05,160 --> 01:00:06,958
l don't. Do l?

719
01:00:07,320 --> 01:00:09,357
No. He's helping me, Menachem.

720
01:00:24,920 --> 01:00:26,832
Open the oven's door.

721
01:00:56,680 --> 01:00:59,195
The sixth day,

722
01:00:59,360 --> 01:01:02,000
all the heavens and earth
were completed.

723
01:01:02,160 --> 01:01:05,676
And God finished His Work
on the seventh day.

724
01:01:05,800 --> 01:01:08,474
And rested on the seventh day
after all He had done.

725
01:01:08,600 --> 01:01:11,718
And God blessed and sanctified
that day, for on it He rested

726
01:01:11,840 --> 01:01:15,038
after all His work which
God created to function.

727
01:01:15,200 --> 01:01:17,271
Together.
- To life.

728
01:01:17,560 --> 01:01:20,792
Blessed are You, king of the
universe, for the fruit of the vine.

729
01:01:20,960 --> 01:01:24,636
Blessed are You, who has sanctified
us with His commandments,

730
01:01:24,760 --> 01:01:27,150
and has given us,
His holy Shabbath as a heritage,

731
01:01:27,280 --> 01:01:31,513
in remembrance of Creation, of
the first Holy Day, of the Exodus.

732
01:01:31,640 --> 01:01:34,155
For You have sanctified
and chosen us from all people.

733
01:01:34,280 --> 01:01:37,557
And Your Holy Shabbath given us
with love and good will.

734
01:01:37,680 --> 01:01:40,115
Blessed are You,
who sanctifies the Shabbath.

735
01:01:40,240 --> 01:01:41,356
Amen.

736
01:01:58,320 --> 01:02:01,154
Blessed are You God,
who brings bread from the earth.

737
01:02:01,280 --> 01:02:02,316
Amen.

738
01:02:24,720 --> 01:02:26,359
Good Shabbath.
- Good Shabbath.

739
01:03:09,120 --> 01:03:12,591
Sorry, l'm a little tired.
l'll be in my room.

740
01:03:12,760 --> 01:03:14,080
Good night.

741
01:03:50,520 --> 01:03:52,989
Have a good meal.
- You too.

742
01:03:58,360 --> 01:04:01,319
Get up, you said we'd wake up early.

743
01:04:01,480 --> 01:04:02,436
ln a bit.

744
01:04:02,600 --> 01:04:04,353
Get up!
- Soon.

745
01:04:04,480 --> 01:04:06,312
Enough sleeping.

746
01:04:06,960 --> 01:04:08,997
Just a little more.

747
01:04:09,480 --> 01:04:10,994
Get up already.

748
01:04:14,840 --> 01:04:17,674
Stop. Just five minutes...

749
01:04:38,240 --> 01:04:40,630
Why didn't you wake me up earlier?
- l did.

750
01:04:46,080 --> 01:04:48,879
Hurry up.
- Hold on, you're going too fast.

751
01:04:54,160 --> 01:04:56,516
Come. Move it!

752
01:04:56,680 --> 01:04:58,319
l am, but you're quick.

753
01:04:59,040 --> 01:05:00,190
lt's hard.

754
01:05:50,160 --> 01:05:52,356
Good Shabbath father.

755
01:05:53,040 --> 01:05:55,316
You ate well?
- What a surprise!

756
01:05:55,800 --> 01:05:59,589
What are you doing here? lt's great.
So good you came!

757
01:06:00,920 --> 01:06:03,230
Good Shabbath.

758
01:06:04,480 --> 01:06:06,039
We were waiting for you.

759
01:06:06,480 --> 01:06:07,914
Bring the books.

760
01:06:10,720 --> 01:06:13,440
Open the weekly Torah portion.

761
01:06:22,760 --> 01:06:25,480
Did it take long to come?
- A long hour.

762
01:06:25,600 --> 01:06:27,717
Not much.
- A long hour?

763
01:06:28,600 --> 01:06:29,795
A long hour...

764
01:06:38,240 --> 01:06:39,560
Have you found it?

765
01:07:02,840 --> 01:07:05,230
"And God spoke to Moses, saying,

766
01:07:05,360 --> 01:07:08,910
"Speak to Aaron and say to him,
When you light the lamps,

767
01:07:09,040 --> 01:07:12,556
"the seven lamps shall give light
over against the candlestick.

768
01:07:12,680 --> 01:07:16,356
"And Aaron did so;
he lighted the lamps

769
01:07:16,480 --> 01:07:20,156
"over against the candlestick,
as God commanded Moses.

770
01:07:20,600 --> 01:07:22,751
"And this work of the candlestick

771
01:07:22,880 --> 01:07:27,909
"was of beaten gold, unto the shaft,
unto the flowers,

772
01:07:28,040 --> 01:07:29,759
"was beaten work,

773
01:07:29,920 --> 01:07:32,196
"according to the pattern
which God had showed Moses,

774
01:07:32,320 --> 01:07:34,312
"so he made the candlestick."

775
01:07:36,480 --> 01:07:37,800
You understood?

776
01:07:38,600 --> 01:07:44,278
Well. When it says:
"Shaft, unto the flower",

777
01:07:44,400 --> 01:07:47,711
what does "Shaft, unto the flower"
mean?

778
01:07:48,400 --> 01:07:52,360
Shaft, down, flower, up.

779
01:07:52,520 --> 01:07:55,911
One piece.
The candlestick was made

780
01:07:56,040 --> 01:07:59,192
of one big piece of gold.

781
01:07:59,320 --> 01:08:00,276
And Grandpa?

782
01:08:00,400 --> 01:08:03,074
Was the candlestick big?
- Very big.

783
01:08:03,320 --> 01:08:05,391
How many branches to it?
- Seven.

784
01:08:05,520 --> 01:08:08,558
Seven, right.
What else is seven?

785
01:08:08,680 --> 01:08:10,399
Days.
- Right.

786
01:08:10,800 --> 01:08:12,314
What's the seventh day?

787
01:08:12,480 --> 01:08:13,994
Shabbath.

788
01:08:15,080 --> 01:08:16,912
These seven days

789
01:08:17,680 --> 01:08:20,878
stand for continuity,

790
01:08:21,880 --> 01:08:24,918
for a whole. Seven days,

791
01:08:25,040 --> 01:08:29,159
then another seven, then, Aaron...

792
01:08:29,720 --> 01:08:32,189
Seven days, and so on.

793
01:08:32,600 --> 01:08:36,196
Eternity. That's Eternity.

794
01:08:36,760 --> 01:08:38,114
And Grandpa?

795
01:08:38,240 --> 01:08:40,038
Will Eternity ever stop?

796
01:08:41,360 --> 01:08:42,350
No.

797
01:08:58,520 --> 01:09:00,079
What do you think?

798
01:09:01,200 --> 01:09:02,759
About what?

799
01:09:03,360 --> 01:09:04,680
Me.

800
01:09:06,800 --> 01:09:08,200
You what?

801
01:09:08,360 --> 01:09:10,636
What do you think about me?

802
01:09:11,160 --> 01:09:12,435
l love you.

803
01:09:14,040 --> 01:09:15,394
Love me?

804
01:09:16,400 --> 01:09:17,720
Love.

805
01:09:20,080 --> 01:09:23,039
l love you too.
- Really?

806
01:09:24,400 --> 01:09:25,436
Yes.

807
01:09:54,240 --> 01:09:55,799
Love me?

808
01:09:56,520 --> 01:09:57,670
Love.

809
01:09:59,360 --> 01:10:03,240
Menachem, wake up! Why didn't you
tell your Mom you were here?

810
01:10:03,360 --> 01:10:05,556
She's very upset. Come, let's go.

811
01:10:05,680 --> 01:10:06,875
Ok.
- Come now.

812
01:10:07,000 --> 01:10:08,320
Ok, fine.

813
01:10:10,160 --> 01:10:12,356
Father, have a good week,
we have to run.

814
01:10:13,200 --> 01:10:16,272
Hold on.
Let me say goodbye properly.

815
01:10:17,000 --> 01:10:19,435
May God bless you, and keep you.

816
01:10:19,640 --> 01:10:22,155
Make His face light you,
and delight you.

817
01:10:22,680 --> 01:10:25,514
May God be present upon you
and give you peace.

818
01:10:26,960 --> 01:10:28,917
Come. Come.
- Goodbye.

819
01:10:51,480 --> 01:10:53,199
Bye bye.
- Bye.

820
01:11:06,840 --> 01:11:08,115
Have a good week.

821
01:11:08,280 --> 01:11:09,270
Good week, Aaron.

822
01:11:09,440 --> 01:11:12,080
You too.
Easy with your mother.

823
01:11:12,840 --> 01:11:14,399
All right.

824
01:11:14,560 --> 01:11:16,358
Bye, you're welcome.

825
01:11:16,840 --> 01:11:19,639
Have a good week.
- Good week.

826
01:11:48,720 --> 01:11:50,439
Menachem, l want to talk to you.

827
01:11:50,960 --> 01:11:52,189
David, go to sleep.

828
01:11:52,600 --> 01:11:54,239
Wait, let me get something to eat.

829
01:11:54,360 --> 01:11:56,113
ln the morning.
- Just a little something.

830
01:11:56,280 --> 01:11:58,875
lt's late, good night.
- Fine.

831
01:12:03,000 --> 01:12:06,152
lt's the last time
you take David without telling me.

832
01:12:06,280 --> 01:12:08,715
Mom, l'm sorry.
- l was so worried.

833
01:12:08,840 --> 01:12:11,196
l apologize.
- l don't need your apology.

834
01:12:11,800 --> 01:12:13,439
Sorry, l should have told you.

835
01:12:13,560 --> 01:12:15,552
Tell me it's the last time.

836
01:12:15,680 --> 01:12:19,640
Ok, l apologized. Good night.
- Sit down.

837
01:12:19,760 --> 01:12:21,558
l wanna sleep, we'll talk tomorrow.

838
01:12:21,680 --> 01:12:24,514
Give me two minutes of your time.
Sit down.

839
01:12:35,400 --> 01:12:36,959
lt can't go on like this.

840
01:12:38,280 --> 01:12:40,033
l know it's hard for you.

841
01:12:41,600 --> 01:12:43,671
For me too. For David too.

842
01:12:46,280 --> 01:12:47,919
But you're not alone.

843
01:12:49,520 --> 01:12:50,840
l'm with you.

844
01:12:51,840 --> 01:12:53,911
And l'm not going anywhere.

845
01:12:54,080 --> 01:12:55,400
Fine.

846
01:12:57,640 --> 01:12:58,756
Yes.

847
01:12:59,680 --> 01:13:01,751
And l miss him too.

848
01:13:07,720 --> 01:13:10,155
l love you most in the world.

849
01:13:11,560 --> 01:13:14,871
And l believe it will be Ok.
Look at me.

850
01:13:17,400 --> 01:13:18,720
l love you.

851
01:13:18,880 --> 01:13:20,758
Good night, Mom.
- Come here.

852
01:13:58,440 --> 01:14:00,557
Ready?
- Just a minute.

853
01:14:05,040 --> 01:14:09,910
l'm afraid Mom will wake up.
- She won't. Don't bring the bag.

854
01:14:10,560 --> 01:14:12,631
lf not, she'll find out.

855
01:14:14,080 --> 01:14:16,675
She'll think l went to school.
- All right.

856
01:14:17,840 --> 01:14:19,320
Pass me the sweatshirt.

857
01:14:27,520 --> 01:14:28,795
Sure about this?

858
01:14:30,640 --> 01:14:31,835
Come, then.

859
01:15:10,200 --> 01:15:13,193
l need you focused.
And stay with me all the time.

860
01:15:28,840 --> 01:15:30,160
Good morning, Aaron.

861
01:15:30,320 --> 01:15:32,039
Morning. How are you?

862
01:15:32,160 --> 01:15:34,800
Can we see the books?
- Are they ready?

863
01:15:34,920 --> 01:15:36,991
They are, but what about school?

864
01:15:37,120 --> 01:15:39,430
We just wanted to see the books...

865
01:15:41,120 --> 01:15:42,031
We came to see them.

866
01:15:42,160 --> 01:15:45,676
Why not after school?
Can't you come after school?

867
01:15:45,840 --> 01:15:48,719
We just wanted to see them,
then we go.

868
01:15:48,840 --> 01:15:50,160
You'll get me in trouble
with your Mom?

869
01:15:50,280 --> 01:15:53,318
No, it's fine. Really.

870
01:15:53,800 --> 01:15:58,556
Ok, look at the books
and run to school.

871
01:15:58,680 --> 01:16:00,478
And while you're there,

872
01:16:00,600 --> 01:16:05,675
put in some requests for prayer,
they're next to the books,

873
01:16:05,840 --> 01:16:09,231
put them inside the Tehilim books.
- No problem.

874
01:16:11,600 --> 01:16:12,795
Quick!

875
01:16:13,720 --> 01:16:15,154
Then to school!

876
01:16:45,560 --> 01:16:47,199
Sit!

877
01:16:49,120 --> 01:16:51,555
"Repentance, Prayer, and Charity",
remember that.

878
01:16:51,840 --> 01:16:54,560
We take these books
and give them to people.

879
01:16:54,680 --> 01:16:57,320
We have to put in
the requests and the money.

880
01:16:57,720 --> 01:17:00,315
We give them
so they can pray for Dad,

881
01:17:00,480 --> 01:17:03,359
they'll give the money for Charity
in his name, got it?

882
01:17:03,520 --> 01:17:04,920
You understand?
- Yes.

883
01:17:05,200 --> 01:17:07,396
So go. Put it in...
- l don't want to.

884
01:17:07,520 --> 01:17:10,194
Sit!
- l want to go home.

885
01:17:10,320 --> 01:17:12,277
Sit!
- You yell at me all the time.

886
01:17:12,440 --> 01:17:14,750
l think we're doing bad things.

887
01:17:14,880 --> 01:17:18,237
lf we're doing something good,
why are you always mad at me?

888
01:17:19,360 --> 01:17:21,511
When you're angry, l feel sad.

889
01:17:23,400 --> 01:17:26,711
l want to go home, l'm scared.
- But l'm not angry.

890
01:17:26,920 --> 01:17:29,276
Why do you give me orders
all the time?

891
01:17:29,400 --> 01:17:33,599
Because l want to do this.
l'm sorry, l'm not angry at you.

892
01:17:33,840 --> 01:17:35,240
You understand?

893
01:17:36,480 --> 01:17:37,834
l... sit down.

894
01:17:38,000 --> 01:17:41,550
l'm sorry if you think l'm mad,
because l'm not.

895
01:17:42,040 --> 01:17:45,317
l just want us to do it together,
you and me,

896
01:17:45,840 --> 01:17:46,956
you understand?

897
01:17:47,120 --> 01:17:50,079
lt's the most important thing
we can do for him.

898
01:17:51,080 --> 01:17:52,434
Will you help me?

899
01:17:53,040 --> 01:17:54,394
Really?

900
01:17:56,440 --> 01:17:58,671
So we're good brothers?
- Yes.

901
01:17:58,960 --> 01:18:01,111
You'll help me?
- Yes.

902
01:18:01,480 --> 01:18:02,800
So, take this.

903
01:18:03,280 --> 01:18:05,590
Put the papers inside.

904
01:18:06,520 --> 01:18:08,716
Ok? You understand?

905
01:18:14,160 --> 01:18:17,232
Take that paper and put it here.

906
01:18:54,520 --> 01:18:57,479
Tehilim for Eli Frankel.
- Pray for Eli Frankel.

907
01:18:58,920 --> 01:19:00,752
We're doing good!
- We are.

908
01:19:02,600 --> 01:19:04,557
Here, sir.
- Sir!

909
01:19:04,680 --> 01:19:07,320
Sir, Tehilim for Eli Frankel.

910
01:19:07,440 --> 01:19:09,159
For what?
- Eli Frankel.

911
01:19:11,000 --> 01:19:14,152
Repair the world with Tehilim,
for Eli Frankel.

912
01:19:14,320 --> 01:19:17,040
Repair the world.
Say the Psalms, pray.

913
01:19:19,760 --> 01:19:21,319
lt's for Eli Frankel.

914
01:19:22,240 --> 01:19:23,435
Here, him.

915
01:19:23,680 --> 01:19:27,117
Tehilim, a present. lt's free.

916
01:19:31,440 --> 01:19:33,716
Give him.
Tehilim for Eli Frankel.

917
01:19:41,120 --> 01:19:43,954
Psalms for Eli Frankel.
To pray for him.

918
01:19:44,560 --> 01:19:46,438
Thank you.
For you, a gift.

919
01:19:46,560 --> 01:19:49,314
You want a donation?
- No, it's free. Thank you.

920
01:19:51,560 --> 01:19:53,199
Give Charity, in his name.

921
01:19:53,360 --> 01:19:55,158
lt's a gift, Tehilim.
- Eli Frankel.

922
01:19:57,120 --> 01:19:58,600
Tehilim, a gift.

923
01:20:00,440 --> 01:20:02,159
Do good, pray and give Charity.

924
01:20:17,160 --> 01:20:19,391
Repentance, Charity, and Prayer
for Eli Frankel.

925
01:20:19,880 --> 01:20:23,954
Thank you very much.
Give to the needy and pray.

926
01:20:24,120 --> 01:20:26,032
Charity and Redemption. Thanks.

927
01:20:29,480 --> 01:20:31,153
Pray for Eli Frankel.

928
01:20:32,720 --> 01:20:34,996
Tehilim. lt's a present.

929
01:20:35,440 --> 01:20:38,797
Excuse me.
Pray.

930
01:20:42,200 --> 01:20:44,476
Hi, Grandpa.
- Hi, kids.

931
01:20:45,200 --> 01:20:47,351
We did good things today.
- Great.

932
01:20:48,120 --> 01:20:49,600
We did everything today.
- Good.

933
01:20:49,720 --> 01:20:50,995
Everything!
- Good.

934
01:20:51,400 --> 01:20:52,470
Aaron!

935
01:20:54,360 --> 01:20:56,238
You have more books?
- Where were you?

936
01:20:56,360 --> 01:20:59,034
No, tell me where you were?
l'd like to know.

937
01:20:59,200 --> 01:21:01,590
Why are you so happy?
l've been waiting for you.

938
01:21:02,440 --> 01:21:04,591
Why are you waiting, we...

939
01:21:05,040 --> 01:21:07,635
Go on, say it, where were you?
l was worried.

940
01:21:07,760 --> 01:21:09,911
What? Where are the books?

941
01:21:11,080 --> 01:21:13,834
We took them.
- We gave them.

942
01:21:13,960 --> 01:21:15,599
To whom?
- To people.

943
01:21:15,720 --> 01:21:17,313
We gave them.
- You gave the books.

944
01:21:17,440 --> 01:21:19,591
We distributed them.
- You distributed them?

945
01:21:19,840 --> 01:21:21,513
Did l ask you to give the books?

946
01:21:21,640 --> 01:21:24,519
l asked you to put the notes in,
not to give them out.

947
01:21:24,640 --> 01:21:27,109
Hold it, l want to understand,

948
01:21:27,440 --> 01:21:28,920
what exactly did you do?

949
01:21:29,080 --> 01:21:31,037
They gave the books,
don't you understand?

950
01:21:31,160 --> 01:21:33,311
To whom did they give them?

951
01:21:35,480 --> 01:21:38,871
Answer me.
To whom did you give the books?

952
01:21:39,040 --> 01:21:42,511
We handed them out on the street.
- What did you do?

953
01:21:43,320 --> 01:21:46,074
You gave them?
- We also put money. -David!

954
01:21:48,680 --> 01:21:50,911
We also put money inside.
- What?

955
01:21:52,560 --> 01:21:54,153
What did you do?
- What?

956
01:21:54,280 --> 01:21:56,033
We put money inside.
- What money?

957
01:21:56,160 --> 01:21:59,358
Which? Where from?
- Which money, Menachem?

958
01:22:01,640 --> 01:22:06,795
Mom has a box with plenty of money
so he took a little.

959
01:22:08,240 --> 01:22:09,674
Did Mom give you money?

960
01:22:09,840 --> 01:22:12,275
Did she, Menachem?
- You are not going.

961
01:22:12,400 --> 01:22:14,835
Mom didn't exactly...
l wanted to do good.

962
01:22:14,960 --> 01:22:18,397
What "not exactly"?
- You took it without permission?

963
01:22:18,600 --> 01:22:19,954
What did you do?

964
01:22:20,280 --> 01:22:24,240
We gave books so people
could be charitable in Dad's name.

965
01:22:25,520 --> 01:22:29,434
To people in the street, like that?
- lt's not like that.

966
01:22:29,560 --> 01:22:32,519
Do you realize
you gave sacred books,

967
01:22:32,640 --> 01:22:37,590
with the name of God,
to people in the street.

968
01:22:37,760 --> 01:22:40,958
Who knows what they'll do?
They might throw it in the trash!

969
01:22:41,080 --> 01:22:42,560
Where did you take that money?

970
01:22:42,960 --> 01:22:47,751
lt was for Repentance and Charity.
- No, no. What Charity?

971
01:22:47,880 --> 01:22:51,237
lt was meant to be given
to your father's community.

972
01:22:51,360 --> 01:22:54,159
Do you understand
you stole a good action?

973
01:22:54,320 --> 01:22:55,390
l was trying to do good.

974
01:22:55,600 --> 01:22:59,150
You're not going anywhere.
You're going to explain it to me...

975
01:22:59,400 --> 01:23:00,959
Do you know what you did?

976
01:23:01,120 --> 01:23:04,352
l was trying to do good.
- Stop him.

977
01:23:04,480 --> 01:23:08,156
We were doing good things.
- Stay here, l'll call your mother.

978
01:23:09,400 --> 01:23:12,996
Hold on, l want to talk to you.
Hold it, where are you going?

979
01:23:13,280 --> 01:23:16,000
Come, there are 150 books left.
We'll give them properly.

980
01:23:16,120 --> 01:23:17,520
l did it for you too.

981
01:23:17,640 --> 01:23:20,917
l understand. You made a mistake.
50 books are gone. lt's done.

982
01:23:21,040 --> 01:23:24,795
Come, there are more books...
- Go, go.

983
01:23:24,920 --> 01:23:26,991
l won't. You come too.
- Leave me alone.

984
01:23:27,120 --> 01:23:30,670
l want you to come too.
Where are you going now?

985
01:24:19,400 --> 01:24:21,153
Yes? Who are you?

986
01:24:21,320 --> 01:24:23,551
l'm Menachem.
- Menachem what?

987
01:24:23,960 --> 01:24:25,792
Frankel.
You're Debbie's father?

988
01:24:25,960 --> 01:24:30,239
Yes, l'm Debbie's father. l heard
that it's over between you two.

989
01:24:30,400 --> 01:24:31,754
You shouldn't be here.

990
01:24:31,880 --> 01:24:33,872
Can you call her?
- Absolutely not.

991
01:24:34,040 --> 01:24:36,032
Just to tell her something.
- No way.

992
01:24:36,200 --> 01:24:38,590
l just want to tell her something.
To talk.

993
01:24:38,720 --> 01:24:40,200
No, she's suffered enough.

994
01:24:40,360 --> 01:24:43,353
lt won't take long.
To say one thing.

995
01:24:43,520 --> 01:24:45,989
l refuse.
- Please let me talk to her.

996
01:24:46,120 --> 01:24:48,794
No, it's hard enough for her now.

997
01:24:48,960 --> 01:24:50,792
l just want to tell her one thing.

998
01:24:50,920 --> 01:24:53,389
No way!
- lt won't take much time.

999
01:24:53,520 --> 01:24:56,558
You shouldn't...
- l just want to tell her...

1000
01:24:56,680 --> 01:24:58,797
Don't ever come back again!

1001
01:26:51,120 --> 01:26:52,270
Mom.

1002
01:27:02,440 --> 01:27:03,635
Mom.

1003
01:27:07,040 --> 01:27:08,394
l'm sorry.

1004
01:27:15,760 --> 01:27:16,910
l'm sorry.

1005
01:30:12,280 --> 01:30:14,158
Here, the documents.

1006
01:30:17,320 --> 01:30:18,515
Excuse me.

1007
01:30:19,840 --> 01:30:21,320
Look,

1008
01:30:22,040 --> 01:30:26,000
this is the report, and the Missing
Person Certificate of your husband.

1009
01:30:26,360 --> 01:30:30,673
With these you can turn to Court,
to the Ministry, whatever you need.

1010
01:30:30,800 --> 01:30:35,477
Please keep them safe,
they're very hard to obtain.

1011
01:30:35,680 --> 01:30:40,709
Now, if you have any question,
you can call this number.

1012
01:30:42,640 --> 01:30:46,520
And of course, if there is
any new information. All right?

1013
01:30:47,520 --> 01:30:48,715
Goodbye.

1014
01:31:47,800 --> 01:31:49,200
